ificant increase in service response time with rrt_max increasing from 7615.0 to 1341060.0 and rrt increasing from 1512.43 to 154447.88.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"The rrt_max and rrt for cartservice-0 showed a large change ratio of approximately 1.98.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Notable increase in rrt_max from 159007.0 to 7648943.0.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"The latency (rrt_max) exhibited a large change, suggesting performance degradation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-06\",\n      \"reason\": \"The node experienced decreased memory usage rate impacting pod performance.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Significant variance in node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes; possibly resource mismanagement.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-05\",\n      \"reason\": \"Memory availability decreased, could have influenced running pods.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Reduction in node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes from 7886508032.0 to 7578365952.0.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```", "trace_analysis_findings": "I have retrieved the trace data for the UUID `53d5d618-289`. Below are the details of the anomalies detected during the period from 2025-06-14T13:10:45Z to 2025-06-14T13:25:45Z:\n\n## Filtered Traces Summary\nThe following services show significant anomalies in terms of duration and frequency:\n\n1. **CheckoutService operations** experienced high delays:\n   - `CartService/EmptyCart` from CheckoutService showed a significant delay, with a normal average duration of 18,245 ms skyrocketing to an anomaly average duration of 3,696,790 ms, appearing 30 times.\n   - `CartService/GetCart` from CheckoutService increased from 8,453 ms to 3,724,258 ms (26 occurrences).\n   - `CheckoutService/PlaceOrder` calls experienced extreme delays across various nodes:\n     - On `aiops-k8s-04` by CheckoutService itself and frontend, delay increased from ~143,518 ms to ~7,312,706 ms (24 occurrences).\n\n2. **Frontend PlaceOrder calls** appeared delayed:\n   - `CheckoutService/PlaceOrder` from frontend to checkoutservice has similar skyrocketing delays in multiple nodes: up to ~7,489,235 ms from ~156,733 ms (18 occurrences).\n   - Another frontend node mentioned with delays from ~148,672 ms to ~7,489,285 ms (17 occurrences).\n\n3. **ShippingService Quote Get** noted some delay:\n   - Various nodes show delays ranging from ~1,944 ms to 4,956 ms (4 occurrences).\n\n4. **ProductCatalogService GetProduct** shows delays too:\n   - With delays from ~11,371 ms to 7,932 ms across nodes (3 occurrences).\n\n5. **CurrencyService Convert** experienced doubled latency:\n   - Spans show latency from ~2,350 ms to 1,352 ms (2 occurrences).\n\n6. **EmailService had reduced delay**\n   - Increased from ~669 ms to 1,549 ms (1 occurrence).\n\n## Unique Entities Involved\nPods:\n- cartservice-2\n- checkoutservice-0\n- checkoutservice-2\n- emailservice-0\n- frontend-0, frontend-1, frontend-2\n- productcatalogservice-2\n\nNodes:\n- aiops-k8s-03, aiops-k8s-04\n- aiops-k8s-06, aiops-k8s-07\n- aiops-k8s-08\n\n## Hypotheses Using Detected Trace Keys\n### Potential Root Causes\n1. **CheckoutService**\n   - Significant delayed performance across CheckoutService indicates a bottleneck root, especially given its catastrophic delay increase during `PlaceOrder`.\n\n2. **Frontend Services**\n   - The delayed operations in `PlaceOrder` suggest frontend interaction lag as well; yet, they all trace back to CheckoutService's primary bottleneck.\n\n3. **Assist Services**\n   - Services like Email and Currency show anomalies but don't fit typical bottleneck or unusual delays, suggesting they could be affected secondarily due to checkoutservice's lag.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\n    \"rrt_max\",\n    \"checkoutservice->cartservice\",\n    \"frontend->checkoutservice\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"CheckoutService\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Mas